        <p data-uuid="a28f84c1cfef448ab822234ac76558b0">Opponents
            of the new Constitution, called <dfn title="Antifederalists">Antifederalists</dfn>, objected to the plan for a
            stronger central government. Supporters of the Constitution, called <dfn title="Federalists">Federalists</dfn>,
            won the public debate by convincing people that the new government would not
            only provide security but also protect their rights.</p>
